Title: Nvidia Blackwell production problems and what was original release date
Description: 
Publish Time: unknown
Content: Nvidia's Blackwell GPU architecture, primarily aimed at data center and AI applications, has faced several production challenges:

1.   Design Flaws: There were reports in August 2024 about design flaws which led to delays in mass production. This issue was related to the processor die that connects two Blackwell GPUs on a single Nvidia GB200 Superchip. The design flaw necessitated a redesign, which was expected to push back the delivery schedule by at least three months or more.
2.   Yield Issues: Nvidia later admitted in August 2024 that its Blackwell-based products were experiencing low production yields. This required a re-spin of some layers of the B200 processor to improve yields, with production ramp-up scheduled for the fourth quarter of 2024.
3.   Overheating Problems: Reports in November 2024 highlighted concerns over overheating when Blackwell GPUs were deployed in server racks, raising issues about their deployment in data centers.
